CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 29, 1946, pg. 22, reads: "From Higher Institutions - Having completed their training in institutions of higher learning, these students are prepared to take over the job of teaching the younger generation... Miss Bernice Johnson, left, and Miss Eva Stanton, both teachers at A. Leo Weil School received M. A. from the University of Pittsburgh..."
TitMainTitle: University of Pittsburgh graduates Bernice Johnson and Eva Stanton, posed with diplomas in front of Cathedral of Learning, Oakland
